Uber South Africa has announced that it will be hiking its prices from 7 December 2018. In a statement, Uber said that while it always tries to keep prices as low as possible, it ‘needs to be aware of the increased costs for driver-partners’. “We’ve chosen to increase fares by 5% in South Africa from 7 December 2018. This comes after implementing an in-depth earnings review to ensure that the Uber app continues to be a reliable economic opportunity for drivers, as well as an affordable option for riders.” The new pricing is as follows: